"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I was told by one of my coworkers that Sprungli was a must-visit for chocolates when I was visiting Zurich, so I made a point of coming here early on Saturday (don&#39;t come Sundays - they are closed) to have ample time to look around and check out all the chocolates. I brought back quite a bit of it with me to the US, but if I have to say one thing that stands out right off, it&#39;s the simple chocolate squares. A lot of places do these, but I don&#39;t think I&#39;ve ever tasted the pure quality of the chocolate in these kinds of pieces as I have from Sprungli. The most impressive, perhaps, are the dark chocolate pieces. I&#39;m usually not a fan of darker chocolates, as most places have pieces that are too bitter, too dry, and lacking in depth of flavor. Here, the 65% and 72% Grand Cru pieces are phenomenal - they just melt in your mouth, with all the richness and breadth of flavor that this kind of chocolate is meant to have. I also love the cylindrical cookies (gaufrettes is what the tag claims they are) filled with chocolate; I would probably go through boxes of these a day if I had gotten more of them - the lightness of the cookie, combined with the dense richness of milk chocolate is so freakin&#39; good.<br><br>The truffles and assorted chocolate pieces are also very well-done, with each piece seemingly hand-crafted and made to perfection. Now I understand why people like Swiss chocolates - and I&#39;m not just talking about Godiva, which seems to be mass-marketed as an upscale brand anywhere around the world. Sprungli&#39;s fare is truly delicious, and I&#39;d recommend getting several of their assorted collections of chocolate goodies, particularly if you&#39;re not from the nearby neighborhood.",
