"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This was a welcome find after wandering around Zurich in the rain. It&#39;s very cute coffee shop although both times we&#39;ve been (both midweek, once around 11am and once around 2:30pm) we&#39;ve gotten the last seats in the entire place. The crowdedness is a little exacerbated by the strollers as well.<br><br>Waffles were unexpected as well as excellent. A little pricey versus back in the US but this is Switzerland, people. <br><br>I would give it 4 stars just because it can be cramped if it weren&#39;t for the first time we went there my 2 year old was getting a little fussy while we starting the &#34;getting ready to go&#34; process (people with children will understand that). One of the waiters nearby saw, grabbed a plate and a squeeze bottle and made this really cute face cartoon out of chocolate on the plate for my little one. She loved it (and proceeded to lick the plate clean) and it struck me as such a nice, out of the way thing for him to do! So 5 stars, super waiter-- you rock!<br><br>Oh, also, dogs are allowed. I beginning to feel like this is common in Switzerland but was a nice little shock for me. If only my dog wasn&#39;t roughly 4,000 miles away.",
