"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/02kQ3MIYK3RGQf3m82FBDA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Awesome food in an unpretentious atmosphere.  I&#39;ve never heard of this place before, but some friends wanted to have dinner here before going to the Eddie Izzard FORCE MAJEURE show at Hallenstadion.  It&#39;s only 1 tram/bus stop away, so really convenient to get dinner here before the show.<br><br>I almost couldn&#39;t find the place, because the yellow stripy awning covered up the sign on the bottom, and it didn&#39;t actually say Rolli in the small letters on top, just steakhouse.  But it&#39;s right next to the Restaurant Metzgerhalle on the corner.<br><br>Inside is kind of decorated in what I would call southern American style with red-and-white checkered tablecloths and old signs on the walls for Yuengling beer and Coca-Cola.  There was one random sign for Haldengut Bier though--which was kind of out of place from all the American stuff.<br><br>I got their special--steak made with American beef with a side of fries and 3 dipping sauces.  The meat was REALLY good.  Perfectly juicy and delicious, with a nice herb-y taste due to some green stuff and tiny red berries on top of the steak.  The meat came out on a hot stone and I could cook it to my own liking.<br><br>The fries were thick-cut and perfectly cooked with a nice taste of potato inside.  Not too salty, like I sometimes find in other places.<br><br>Dipping sauces were really rich and creamy, with great flavor.  A curry one, a garlic one, and a pinkish one kind of like Thousand Island.<br><br>4 of us shared a bottle of Cabernet Sauvignon from California.  My dinner cost SFr. 50 for the meal and sharing the wine.  This was probably the best steak I&#39;ve had in Switzerland so far in 3.5 years.",
