"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/BPEg1TXsAJlqraqtrkwsng/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I really feel the need to update my review for Don Weber, even if I won&#39;t change its full 5 stars rating.<br>We went there on a Saturday evening 8pm, genuinely hoping to get seats. Of course it didn&#39;t work, as they were almost full and there were many reservations pending. Instead, we were invited to sit at the bar and wait for free tables.<br>The service was well intended, but there were only 3 people for the entire place, including the bar, which made the service messy. After waiting for half an hour, we were finally seated. It was a bit frustrating I agree, but the lively atmosphere made us get over it quite quickly.<br><br>We then ordered the food and drinks. Drinks arrived quickly, but food took veery long. Then, after 45 minutes of waiting, they offered us a shot from the house, to apologize for the long wait. We found this to be a very nice gesture.<br><br>Food came soon after. I found bit weird that my quesadilla was with chorizo rather than chicken (as I had ordered), but I didn&#39;t complain as it was actually very tasty. Then, after we were finished with our meal, they came with a second serving... another quesadilla for me (chicken this time) and burger with fries for my boyfriend. We were really puzzled. They told us that&#39;s from the house as well, still apologizing for their delay in bringing us the food. My boyfriend was really full from his burger, so didn&#39;t have the second serving. Nevertheless, we got the chicken quesadilla, which we actually found to be not as good as the chorizo one. However, I wouldn&#39;t have ordered that by myself, so I am happy that it all happened this way.<br><br>I was particularly impressed with their way of apologizing. I enjoy the place, the food, the people.. Will for sure go back!",
