"reviewcomment":"I found on this place by accident as I was looking with some friends for a nice brunch place on a Sunday afternoon but the place recommended to me was closed. We spotted the café because of its terrace and the young clientele.<br><br>The place is really nice, with this retro look that draws Hipsters like a magnet. It is located in front of the Fritschiwiese Park so if you&#39;re bored you can always have a look at the people in the park :P<br><br>We had a Bircher muesli, cappuccinos, croissants, scrambled eggs, bacon and some bread. The Bircher muesli was really good, and there was more than enough of it J I think I had never seen so many toppings on a single Bircher: I remember at least blackberries, blueberries, strawberries, raisins and 3 different sorts of nuts. It was a delight J My friends also liked their eggs, bacon and croissants. The only bad note here were the cappuccinos, as they came warm.<br><br>Although prices were aligned with Zurich prices, I must say that my biggest complaint is the service. We had an unfriendly waiter who was confused on who ordered what, and each time we had to wait a lot to be served (maybe that&#39;s why our cappuccinos came warm). And it&#39;s not like the place was full.<br><br>I would go back again for a beer or so (I have seen that they also serve nice Belgian beers) or even have dinner there but I hope that next time the service will be a bit more efficient and friendly.",
