"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/s-ZznL6zraFKL8rvSMktwg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I went there for a business lunch, I took one of their daily menus, they have many ranging from 22 to around 50 CHF though I did not look that much to the high prices. <br><br>I chose the second one, for 27 CHF, which did not include meet. It included a salad or a soup plus a main dish, which turned out to be spinach cannelloni with tomato sauce (I say, &#34;turned out&#34; because my German is still basic and the daily menu is only in German and Italian).<br><br>I chose the salad which was a small Insalata Caprese (would be less fancy to say tomatoes with mozzarella, right?), with a light dressing. You will of course find Italian balsamic vinegar and olive oil at your table, so it&#39;s not an issue to arrange the dressing to your liking. Onward to the cannelloni, portions are sufficient (you will get around 3-4) and you get plenty of sauce. The cannelloni are well cooked and tasty, same goes for the sauce and the parmigiano.<br><br>Regarding the overall appraisal of the place, the atmosphere is classy and the chairs are comfortable. Staff is friendly though not that much responsive which might have been cause by the amount of people present in the restaurant. It also led to a quite high noise level (acoustics do not seem to have been part of the construction design).<br><br>Overall, I would still give it a five due the decent service and price for the location.",
