"reviewcomment":"I&#39;m only guilty of not ordering a larger portion of tasty soup.  I had the standard Dal soup with a smattering of cilantro as garnish. A tasty roll was also included.  The soup was flavorful, piping hot, and went down a treat with the bread roll.  After perusing their website, it would seem that NG is a part of the &#39;locavore&#39; movement, using, when possible, locally sourced ingredients.  Also nice, the service is friendly and prompt.    <br><br>One of the most interesting things about NG would be that they have three restos in ZH and one in Brazil!  Por que?  I aim to find out on my next trip to Not Guilty.<br><br>Note: the soup sizes don&#39;t read &#39;small&#39; and &#39;large&#39; on the menu board.  I forget what the cutesy language is...something like &#39;good day&#39; for a small soup and for a larger soup it&#39;s something equally silly.  Don&#39;t be discouraged as I was for a fraction of a second when trying to absorb the menu.  There are only two sizes: good and gooder. ;)",
