"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/EQYOCVv3LKtKtvXLf12kYA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve been here two times both due to the good reviews and the central location. I&#39;m speaking about the central location because, as you know, I usually lack time so I try to meet people close to their destination, often the main station.<br><br>I&#39;ve tried two types of beverage so far here, some kind of coffee of which I don&#39;t remember the name due to the fact that I don&#39;t drink much coffee. But it was good and served with a glass of water (5,- CHF) always handy when you don&#39;t get much to drink the rest of the day. Was fine but once again I&#39;m not pro.<br>I&#39;ve also tested their Earl Grey tea (I&#39;m more into that kind of things). Was pretty cool for an acceptable price in Zurich (4,5 CHF).<br><br>The place is quite clean and got good chairs/ tables. If you go for the high one you can conveniently drop your coat/other stuff one the small wall close to the tables. Careful however, there is not much room between tables, so try to pick a seat quick on those. Alternatively there are se couches that seemed cool as well.<br><br>Staff is friendly and efficient. They won&#39;t bother you but might ask if you need something else from time to time which is absolutely fine.",
