"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I stayed at this property for a business trip and meeting site inspection in mid October 2013. The property was immaculate and the rooms were well appointed. I had a very business atmosphere with all the amenities you need. <br>I must say that the staff was amazing! They were on top of my every need, from restaurant recommendations, which were so on the money, to travel arrangements to shopping locations. From the moment I checked into this hotel I felt welcomed. <br>I took a massage during my stay that was excellent. <br>Let&#39;s talk views...from everywhere. while having a massage, I was able to enjoy a perfect vista from the table. <br>The meeting space was incredible. There are 2 floors of meeting space. One on the lower with larger ballroom type spaces, (which can be divided) and then there is the upstairs for the smaller group meetings. Again...la bella vista! from every room. All state of the art and very typical Swiss style. Great areas to dine. <br>The sales team was amazing as well. They knew their inventory and their product and were able to point me in the right direction for my needs. <br>The restaurant was good, breakfast was a fantastic buffet, with everything for carnivores and vegetarians alike. <br>The only downside is the security of the internet. My internet was hacked during my stay, which can happen, (and has happened as a road warrior), to anyone. No matter, that is not a good experience. <br>. <br>The beds were comfortable enough and inline with European standards. It was too late that I realized they had a pillow menu. Mine were way too soft for me...so be sure to enquire. <br>Overall, great experience",
