"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Went here for dinner with the BF and had a nice meal :)<br>I ordered the penne bolognese but penne is prob my least favorite pasta shape so I asked them to sub the penne for spaghetti and they did. Before our meal we shared the nüsslisalat which was really really good. They also brought out a small bruchetta with tomatoes and mozzarella and a little shot sized fresh squeezed blood orange juice. It is little things like that they make me want to go back..<br>However, our service was just not good. :( He mumbled and spoke so quietly that it was hard to know what he said (and that is not just because I am a non native german speaker) and then when my pasta arrived they didn&#39;t offer any parmesan cheese, nor did it come with any, but I saw all the other tables get some :( and he didn&#39;t come back over so I didn&#39;t get the chance to ask. My BF was also not given any chili oil for his pizza which the other tables were also offered. So silly because my pasta was good without it, but could have been great with it. <br>Overall I was very happy with the food. Our bottle of mineral water cost us 14CHF though, so bring your own! Kidding.... but really... 14chf???!! for some san pellegrino..? :/",
