"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/MyP125k5pPXZWnOFBioOow/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"We took an out-of-town friend to Khan&#39;s because I was expecting to get the quality food &amp; service experience I had when I had gone there with a Khan&#39;s regular customer. Needless to say, we were treated like tourists who&#39;d probably never come back there(they&#39;re right about that).<br><br> We ordered two vegetable Samosas, the butter chicken, a Tandoori platter, and of course Naan. We also ordered a 70CHF bottle of white wine, which our waiter promptly spilled onto the table when filling the glasses. Our entire order arrived 5 minutes after we placed the order. And all at once! After placing all the food on the table, the waiter would not leave. Instead, he began serving us pieces from the Tandoori platter and by the time we were served our food was already cold. Maybe it was cold to start with.<br><br> The Tandoori platter was the most disappointing dish that I&#39;ve had in the past year in Switzerland. I highly recommend you avoid it. I am embarrassed to have recommended this place to our friend who picked up the check",
