"reviewcomment":"Ah, the Zeughauskeller. A restaurant so prominent and well-placed, it&#39;s a stop in almost every tourist setting foot in this adorable little city.<br><br>And there&#39;s generally no reason to blame them. The interior is well-done and tries to give the impression of historic relevance. It&#39;s maybe trying a bit too hard to do so, which results in a certain cheesiness, but I think it&#39;s generally well-received by the customers frequenting this establishment.<br><br>People come here to eat what they consider &#34;traditional&#34; local food. I&#39;ll leave it to others to judge if what you are served here is actually traditional, but the couple of times I&#39;ve been here, the last time being a week ago, I ate well and I didn&#39;t pay an extraordinary amount of money, considering that we&#39;re still talking about a restaurant that is located right next to the Paradeplatz.<br><br>Service is a bit hit-or-miss and generally better when you reserve a table in advance.",
