"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Outstanding Italian cuisine.  <br><br>The menu of the day was heavy on venison; we ended up with a venison ragout, which was tender and savory, but was still distinctively not beef.  Certainly mellow and not gamey --- perhaps farmed venison?<br><br>The smaller plates we ordered --- pasta fagioli (potted pasta with beans) and risotto --- were savory and made you feel like you were visiting someone&#39;s family.<br><br>Even the insalata mista and mortadella were nicely above average.<br><br>Desserts were each good, and balanced each other nicely.  The torta della casa was a fairly straight-ahead dense chocolate cake, and the tartufa di limoncello was bizarre --- crispy lemony outside, fluffy lemon fluff (somewhere between gelato and marshmallow), and a dense lemon-curd-jelly core.<br><br>Service was excellent, attentive, and managed a health emergency from another customer with a nice balance of efficiency and aplomb.  The reservation system involves a website, some text messages, and no waiting on hold --- I&#39;m a fan.<br><br>Their website even includes a Tetris game.  Who does that?",
