"reviewcomment":"It&#39;s been a while since I had fish cooked so perfectly as the one I had there (it was called Gurame goreng bumbu kuning). Amazing. The others had the beef (Rendang) which had the most interesting combination of spices in the sauce, such a unique taste! <br><br>The chef came out to check on us and chat about the food and the place, and I have the same comment as the fish - it had been MONTHS since I received such outstanding service. To me, the excellence of the food and the highest standards of service more than justify the price in this case. I would say though, that CHF 60 (tip included) for two cokes, an appetizer, a very generous main dish, a side dish of rice, and a dessert it&#39;s an excellent value here in Zurich!<br><br>I went back for the 11-course meal called rijsttafel - inquire with the restaurant and book at least 24 hours in advance.<br><br>Thumbs up for Dapur Indonesia from me!!!",
