"reviewcomment":"Went on a summer evening for drinks at the bar, then dinner, both outdoors. The ambiance in the outside bar area is great - there are lounge chairs and bar stools. The whole area is very chic, romantic, comfortable. Great cocktails. <br><br>The outdoor dining area is over the water and you get great views of the sunset over the lake with dinner. Food was good - a bit on the pricier side but you expect that since its Zurich, and because of the restaurant&#39;s location. Fish was cooked perfectly - crispy skin and juicy everything else - and seasoned lightly but well. Servings were substantial. Service is good. <br><br>(In terms of value though I did witness a local woman losing it - crying - because she ordered a $70+ lobster dish and they only served her half the lobster. I ordered a $50 fish dish and got only a filet...is that comparable?) <br><br>(Also...we had a reservation but did not have a per person minimum enforced against us. They did however seat us about 20 minutes after our reserved time)",
