"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Even though you have never been here, you know this restaurant already; it&#39;s the kind of place where you get lulled by cheesy Argentinian muzak and the dimly-lit lights together with the over-dominance of the color red giving you the impression of accidentally having entered a Twin-peaky dream sequence. You feel awkward and right at home at the same time. A little like going to your estranged aunts place as an adult where you used to go to in the summer when you were a kid.<br><br>But let&#39;s get real. The food is ok, but nothing to write home about (note the irony of me writing home about it? Good. Let&#39;s move on.) As some of my fellow yelpers have noted, the staff is really friendly, if also a little on the slow side. The all-you-can-eat spareribs (only with a deindeal voucher) were tasty-ish, but nothing you would want to all-you-can-eat of. The star of the meal for me were the extremely yummy sweet potatoe fries, which have been unparalleled in CH for me thus far! I think they are the monthly special though, so get them while you can!",
