"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I was very pleasantly surprised by this find (thank you Yelp!).  It was my first night in Zurich and I just needed/wanted some Italian comfort food.  However, I was traveling alone and wanted to make sure I felt comfortable dining alone.  <br><br>My server greeted me at the door and as soon as he realized I spoke English he responded in kind (I do not speak German).  He escorted me to a table fit for 1 and brought me a menu in English.<br><br>The caprese salad was outstanding... excellent mozzarella and tomatoes, fresh basil and wonderful olive oil as well.<br><br>I ordered the penne with puttanesca and it was wonderful.  A very large portion - I had to take part of it with me.<br><br>I ordered a white wine, which was very nice.<br><br>The service was good by European standards... sometimes I think we get over-served in the US, so it was good.  You definitely have to ask for your check, but again, in the US sometimes they rush you out the door, so to be able to just sit and enjoy was nice.",
