"reviewcomment":"The best North and South Indian restaurant in Zürich. The service was very friendly. When we came in, it was not very busy. All the tables were reserved. We had a tip from someone we know. The restaurant was easy to reach by tram and it was a bit outside Zürich. You can go with the tram or bus. We were with the tram 13 and the tram stops in front of the restaurant. The restaurant is above a store. When we came in we see a cosy interor with typical Indian stuffs. It was a bit too much, too full and old for me. But it was in one style. The chairs were not too comfortable. You have to sit too straight. You have a big choice from the menu. A lots of diffirent dishes from the north and south India. The proportions were good. A good thing was also that they put the dishes on a hotplate and candles. The service was a bit to fast. But above all it was a good diner (i ate to much) I will certainly come back.",
