"reviewcomment":"Nested right off the Rennweg tram stop is a &#34;mixed&#34; restaurant with a casual sit down area. It gets four stars for offering a variety for the patron who hasn&#39;t made up his/her mind about what to eat!<br><br>The store is sectioned in different areas, based on different types of food. Right in the front of the store is the made for take out foods, such as sandwiches (which there is a turkey sandwich with mango sauce that I like), salads, wraps and sushi/sashimi. I normally get the fast option of sashimi (available in salmon, tuna or both) with rice and a miso soup - the sushi/sashimi are priced well and are of ok quality (vs buying your sushi from Migros/Coop, eek). There is also a hot foods buffet (Asian) but it can be pricey so watch how much you pile on! Inside there is a Japanese noodle soup area, which I have tried once - it is okay, but nothing to die for.",
