"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Another great place in Oerlikon, very close to Chayenne and with quite similar food (Mexican profile) is Tres Amigos. I think the fact that these two very similar restaurants are so close to eachother and still manage to be full almost every nice in a suburb of Zurich is an indication that they do indeed serve good stuff :)<br>One advantage over Chayenne is that they serve food all day long, even between lunch time and dinner time (Chayenne only serves snacks then). <br><br>We visited the place twice. Once we ordered fajitas and it was just enough for two people and the other time I ordered a chicken burrito (it was huge), while my boyfriend had something like beef with lemon and tequila sauce. I liked the food every time and will definitely go back.<br><br>Prices are high, but that&#39;s Zurich...<br><br>P.S: great Apfel strudel as well :)",
